      "repair_reason": "- No automated repair is identified; maintainers should decide whether to accept the intentional history-splitting upgrade behavior before merge.; Cleared: No concrete security or supply-chain regression found; the diff adds no dependencies or scripts and persists only a namespaced hash-derived account key, not token material. (sha=48d0cd6a3149672bd3d1e91e12f29f450afa7f2d)",
      "review_summary": "The PR scopes Claude OAuth plan-utilization history to a hashed stable Keychain persistent reference, falls identityless OAuth samples back to unscoped history, and adds focused regression/keychain tests.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source-level reproduction rather than a live Keychain switch: the linked issue shows identityless Claude OAuth samples can reuse a stale preferred bucket on current main, and this PR adds regression tests for that path. I did not run live provider validation because AGENTS.md warns against Keychain-prompting checks.",
